title: HP ProLiant: Smart Array / RAID Controllers (phantom-row fix)
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/server/hp
author: Kuhn & Rueß GmbH <info@kuhn-ruess.de>
license: GPL
distribution: none
description:
 Drop-in replacement for the built-in {hp_proliant_da_cntlr} check. It
 monitors the condition, board condition and board status of HP/HPE ProLiant
 Smart Array / RAID controllers read from the {cpqDaCntlrTable}
 (.1.3.6.1.4.1.232.3.2.2.1.1) and behaves exactly like the shipped check for
 real controllers.

 It additionally fixes a discovery problem seen on ProLiant Gen11 systems
 managed via iLO 6: their controller table contains a phantom/placeholder row
 (typically at index 0) whose condition, board status and board condition
 cells are all "0". The vendor MIB has no "0" enum value, so this is not a
 real controller. The built-in check discovers a service for that row anyway
 and then reports it as {UNKNOWN} ("Controller not found in SNMP data") on
 every check cycle. This override skips such all-zero rows already during
 discovery, so no bogus "HW Controller 0" service is created.

 This plugin re-registers the section and check under the original name
 {hp_proliant_da_cntlr} and therefore shadows the built-in version. Remove
 the package once the upstream check skips phantom rows itself.

item:
 The controller index from the {cpqDaCntlrTable}, e.g. "23".

inventory:
 One service per controller that reports valid (non-zero) condition and
 status cells. Phantom/placeholder rows are not discovered.
